   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>The first patch should have a data migration. See
<a href="http://south.aeracode.org/docs/tutorial/part3.html">http://south.aeracode.org/docs/tutorial/part3.html</a> and read the section
beginning, "Now, the second migration is more interesting".

You should copy over the trivial project save logic into the migration:

for project in orm.Project.objects.all():
   if not project.display_name:
       project.display_name = project.other_field
       project.save()
(as a rough sketch)

Other than that, these look good. They took me a while to understand.

The /search/ stuff in views.py and controllers.py looks okay to me; that's just
user-facing stuff.

If the test pass once you resubmit, I'll push and deploy.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
