  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Done:
<a href="http://git.jackgrigg.com/openhatch/patch/?id=d2054956f629e321a0748def548304b47532b752">http://git.jackgrigg.com/openhatch/patch/?id=d2054956f629e321a0748def548304b47532b752</a>
<a href="http://git.jackgrigg.com/openhatch/patch/?id=992b36627a3465615811ef3ca6967d47a86fb5e9">http://git.jackgrigg.com/openhatch/patch/?id=992b36627a3465615811ef3ca6967d47a86fb5e9</a>

After applying the first patch, run the following in "./bin/mysite shell_plus":

for project in Project.objects.all()
    project.save()

That will set the display_name field for all Projects to be the same as the name
field rather than blank, so that when the second patch is applied /search/
doesn't fail because every project has the same display_name of ''.

Also, see my comments in the second patch. I am not sure if this is a problem or
not - in some ways it seems better, and in others worse. But I really don't know
the search code, so I am really placed to say much.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
